<subSubSection id="52A4656CF104994EB3C7FD79FCBABA84" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1A0136E7F104994EB3C7FD79FCB0BB9A" blockId="11.[140,1108,553,1002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">
Newly recorded on 
<collectingRegion id="D87AF805F104994EB2EBFD79FD01BBBE" box="[405,647,694,720]" country="Canada" name="Prince Edward Island" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">Prince Edward Island</collectingRegion>
, this species favours temporary pools and muddy or weedy margins of ponds or lakes (
<bibRefCitation id="7E2F4B16F104994EB1FFFD15FCACBB9A" author="Smetana A" box="[641,810,730,756]" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" pagination="1 - 316" refId="ref9991" refString="Smetana A (1988) Review of the family Hydrophilidae of Canada and Alaska (Coleoptera). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada 142: 1 - 316." type="journal article" year="1988">Smetana 1988</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1A0136E7F104994EB3C7FD32FCBABA84" blockId="11.[140,1108,553,1002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">
This adventive, Palaearctic species was first reported in North America by 
<bibRefCitation id="7E2F4B16F104994EB08CFD32FE8BBA54" author="Darlington PJ, Jr" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" pagination="174 - 175" refId="ref8731" refString="Darlington PJ, Jr (1927) Helophorus aquaticus L. in America. Psyche 34: 174 - 175." type="journal article" year="1927">Darlington (1927)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="7E2F4B16F104994EB265FCEFFE54BA55" author="Smetana A" box="[283,466,800,827]" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" pagination="1 - 154" refId="ref9958" refString="Smetana A (1985) Revision of the subfamily Helophorinae of the Nearctic region (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada 131: 1 - 154." type="journal article" year="1985">Smetana (1985)</bibRefCitation>
examined specimens from as early as 1904 from Montreal, although 
<bibRefCitation id="7E2F4B16F104994EB244FC8BFE5ABA33" author="Brown WJ" box="[314,476,835,862]" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" pagination="65 - 78" refId="ref8642" refString="Brown WJ (1940) Notes on the American distribution of some species of Coleoptera common to the European and North American continents. Th e Canadian Entomologist 72: 65 - 78." type="journal article" year="1940">Brown (1940)</bibRefCitation>
noted a specimen from Chicoutimi, 
<collectingRegion id="D87AF805F104994EB0F6FC8CFC65BA33" box="[904,995,835,861]" country="Canada" name="Quebec" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">Québec</collectingRegion>
, from the “second” collection of Provancher acquired sometime between 
<date id="6E001027F104994EB01AFCA8FB9DBAEF" box="[868,1051,870,897]" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" value="1877" valueMax="1892">1877 and 1892</date>
. The earliest records from 
<collectingRegion id="D87AF805F104994EB20BFC45FDAFBACA" box="[373,553,906,932]" country="Canada" name="New Brunswick" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">New Brunswick</collectingRegion>
are in 1926 and from 
<collectingRegion id="D87AF805F104994EB05AFC45FC2ABACA" box="[804,940,906,932]" country="Canada" name="Nova Scotia" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">Nova Scotia</collectingRegion>
in 1947 (
<bibRefCitation id="7E2F4B16F104994EB766FC45FF78BAA6" author="Smetana A" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" pagination="1 - 154" refId="ref9958" refString="Smetana A (1985) Revision of the subfamily Helophorinae of the Nearctic region (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada 131: 1 - 154." type="journal article" year="1985">Smetana 1985</bibRefCitation>
) so the collection from 1923 on 
<collectingRegion id="D87AF805F104994EB116FC62FCD1BAA9" box="[616,855,941,967]" country="Canada" name="Prince Edward Island" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">Prince Edward Island</collectingRegion>
establishes a new early timeline for 
<taxonomicName id="DDBE4D64F104994EB266FC1EFE0DBA84" authority="Illiger, 1798" box="[280,395,976,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Helophoridae" genus="Helophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis id="28CAEAF5F104994EB266FC1EFE0DBA84" box="[280,395,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">H. grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Maritime Provinces of 
<collectingCountry id="62A97677F104994EB1A0FC1FFCBEBA84" box="[734,824,976,1002]" name="Canada" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">Canada</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
